25/02/2022, 13:33 - hitesh jnu: Determine the number of additions and multiplications if the matrices are all n x n.
iska??
25/02/2022, 13:33 - Arvind Jnu: Flag
A complex-valued matrix X is represented by a pair of matrices (A, B) where A and B contains real values.

You have to write a C++program that computes the product of two complex-valued matrices (A, B) and (C, D), where (A, B) * (C, D) = (A+iB)*(C+iD) = (AC-BD)+i(AD + BC).

Observing your C++ program and determine the number of additions and multiplications if the matrices are all nxn.

07/03/2022, 19:43 - Aditya Mahakali: proposed draft, 


To,  scss_office@jnu.ac.in    chair_scss@jnu.ac.in     dean_scss@jnu.ac.in 

Subject: To request for hostel allotment for mca student from next semester in may
Respected sir,

It's been almost 2 years since we students are taking classes online, away from the vibrant and exciting campus. Now, since all other campuses in the country have switched to offline mode, we are expecting our classes to go back offline as well. MCA is a 2-year course, half of the year got wasted due to COVID, we are inching to be left with just a year and still no offline classes. 

Online class quality is not up to the JNU name, internet disconnections, voice, and video breakage because of slow internet. Teaching via ppt and books feels incomplete because of lack of explanation via examples, although this particular problem can be partially solved by providing good quality pen-tablet to teachers. We also do not have any desired lab sessions in online mode. Development of communication skills is also stagnant due to the past 2 years of covid, we want to explore the JNU opportunity. 

We request the school to please ensure that all of us are allotted hostels in the next semester starting from May, many of us come from not-so-privileged backgrounds and rely upon the JNU hostels and mess facility. We fear that if the process of hostel allotment starts late for our school many of us will not get hostels. This fear comes from the fact that we do not have any information regarding how many rooms are reserved for mca students or the hostel allotment is based on first come first(This info is from students residing in JNU hostels).

Many of us donâ€™t have a good educational environment in our homes, we donâ€™t have access to books and thus wish to fully utilize library facilities which provide both the material and environment for study. 
So, we kindly request you to resolve our concerns so that we can join JNU classes offline and make use of all the facilities of the hostel, library, etc. 
We are requesting this because the earlier told date of June 30 will be very late as our placement season is supposed to start in about august-September. Preparation can be better for us in offline mode because of mutual help. Please complete our physical verification and hostel allotment as early as possible.

Thanking you

Yours truly
Masoom baccha/bacchi
Enrollment number

To,  scss_office@jnu.ac.in    chair_scss@jnu.ac.in     dean_scss@jnu.ac.in 

Subject: To request for hostel allotment for mca student from next semester in may
Respected sir,

It's been almost 2 years since we students are taking classes online, away from the vibrant and exciting campus. Now, since all other campuses in the country have switched to offline mode, we are expecting our classes to go back offline as well. MCA is a 2-year course, half of the year got wasted due to COVID, we are inching to be left with just a year and still no offline classes. 

Online class quality is not up to the JNU name, internet disconnections, voice, and video breakage because of slow internet. Teaching via ppt and books feels incomplete because of lack of explanation via examples, although this particular problem can be partially solved by providing good quality pen-tablet to teachers. We also do not have any desired lab sessions in online mode. Development of communication skills is also stagnant due to the past 2 years of covid, we want to explore the JNU opportunity. 

We request the school to please ensure that all of us are allotted hostels in the next semester starting from May, many of us come from not-so-privileged backgrounds and rely upon the JNU hostels and mess facility. We fear that if the process of hostel allotment starts late for our school many of us will not get hostels. This fear comes from the fact that we do not have any information regarding how many rooms are reserved for mca students or the hostel allotment is based on first come first(This info is from students residing in JNU hostels).

Many of us donâ€™t have a good educational environment in our homes, we donâ€™t have access to books and thus wish to fully utilize library facilities which provide both the material and environment for study. 
So, we kindly request you to resolve our concerns so that we can join JNU classes offline and make use of all the facilities of the hostel, library, etc. 
We are requesting this because the earlier told date of June 30 will be very late as our placement season is supposed to start in about august-September. Preparation can be better for us in offline mode because of mutual help. Please complete our physical verification and hostel allotment as early as possible.

Thanking you

Yours truly
Masoom baccha/bacchi
Enrollment number

16/03/2022, 12:50 - Mohit Jnu: //matrix multiplication

#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    int r1,c1,r2,c2,rows,columns,i,j,k;
    printf("Enter the number of rows and columns of matrix 1 :\n");
    scanf("%d %d",&r1,&c1);
    int a[r1][c1];
    printf("Enter the elemnets in matrix 1 :\n");
    for(i=1;i<=r1;i++)
    {
        for(j=1;j<=c1;j++)
        { 
         printf(" the element a[%d][%d] is :",i,j);
         scanf("%d",&a[i][j]);
        }
    } 
    
    printf("The matrix 1 is:\n");
    for(i=1;i<=r1;i++)
    {
        for(j=1;j<=c1;j++)
        { 
         
         printf("%d\t",a[i][j]);
        }
        printf("\n");
    } 
         
    
    printf("Enter the number of rows and columns of matrix 2 :\n");
    scanf("%d %d",&r2,&c2);
    int b[r2][c2];
    printf("Enter the elemnets in matrix 2 :\n");
    for(i=1;i<=r2;i++)
    {
        for(j=1;j<=c2;j++)
        { 
         printf(" the element b[%d][%d] is :",i,j);
         scanf("%d",&b[i][j]);
        }
        
    } 
    
    printf("The matrix 2 is:\n");
     for(i=1;i<=r2;i++)
    {
        for(j=1;j<=c2;j++)
        { 
         
         printf("%d\t",b[i][j]);
        }
       printf("\n"); 
    } 
    
    
    if(c1==r2)
    {
        printf("Multiplication is possible ...\n");
        int c[rows][columns];
        
        for(i=1;i<=r1;i++){
            for(j=1;j<=c2;j++){
                c[i][j]=0;}
        }
            
        for(i=1;i<=r1;i++){
            for(j=1;j<=c2;j++){
                for(k=1;k<=r2;k++){
                c[i][j] += a[i][k]*b[k][j];
                }
            }
        }
         
        printf("The matrix after multiplication is :\n");
        for(i=1;i<=r1;i++){
            for(j=1;j<=c2;j++){
                
                    printf("%d\t",c[i][j]);
                
                
            }
            printf("\n");
        }
        
        
        
    }
    else {
        printf("Multiplication is not possible!!!");
    }
    
}

We have a general request to everyone.
Assignment related, attendance related aur even teachers ke tasks related, humse jitna ho raha hai, hum kar rahe hai, website pe daal dete hai, aur MCA imp pe bhi daal diya karte hai.
lekin, humare batch mein ek responsibility wali approach missing hai.
like, online classes mein bahut log attend karte hai, aur hum assignment ya task group pe, website pe bhi daal dete hai, phir bhi students DM karke chhote chhote details puchte hai,
(kabhi kabhi difficult ho jata hai, saare DMs ka instant reply karna, but hum try karte hai.) toh ek baari group mein puch liya karo.
project related/ya test related, hum teachers se puchte hai, but jab unki classes hoti hai, toh tum bhi puch liya karo koi particular query hai toh. Online classes mein direct interaction toh kar hi sakte hai na.
aur course ke WhatsApp group mein jo activity ho raha hai, follow karte raho.
like Gayen sir ka DSA group mein text aaya tha, unke 2 baar puchne par hi sab reply kar rahe the, Piyush sir ka C group mein abhi tak sir ke last question ka reply nahi kiya gaya hai.

toh ye request hai ki saare minute reminders dene ki puri responsibility humare hi upar hai, aisa karna feasible nahi hota hai.
toh, khudke upar bhi kuch zimedaari le ke chaloge toh sabke liye beneficial hoga.

06/04/2022, 13:52 - Aditya Mahakali: Respected sir,

It's been almost 2 years since we students are taking classes online, away from the vibrant and exciting campus. Now, since all other campuses in the country have switched to offline mode, we are expecting our classes to go back offline as well. MCA is a 2-year course, half of the year got wasted due to COVID, we are inching to be left with just a year and still no offline classes. 

Online class quality is not up to the JNU name, internet disconnections, voice, and video breakage because of slow internet. Teaching via ppt and books feels incomplete because of lack of explanation via examples, although this particular problem can be partially solved by providing good quality pen-tablet to teachers. We also do not have any desired lab sessions in online mode. Development of communication skills is also stagnant due to the past 2 years of covid, we want to explore the JNU opportunity. 

We request the school to please ensure that all of us are allotted hostels in the next semester starting from May, many of us come from not-so-privileged backgrounds and rely upon the JNU hostels and mess facility. We fear that if the process of hostel allotment starts late for our school many of us will not get hostels. This fear comes from the fact that we do not have any information regarding how many rooms are reserved for mca students or the hostel allotment is based on first come first(This info is from students residing in JNU hostels).

Many of us donâ€™t have a good educational environment in our homes, we donâ€™t have access to books and thus wish to fully utilize library facilities which provide both the material and environment for study. 
So, we kindly request you to resolve our concerns so that we can join JNU classes offline and make use of all the facilities of the hostel, library, etc. 
We are requesting this because the earlier told date of June 30 will be very late as our placement season is supposed to start in about august-September. Preparation can be better for us in offline mode because of mutual help. Please complete our physical verification and hostel allotment as early as possible.

Thanking you

Yours truly

Advantages/Disadvantages bit
22/04/2022, 12:16 - Harshita jnu: Structures are better than Unions in almost every case.

The only time when a union is better than a struct is if you will have an array of unnamed objects, and you want to save space.

For example, if you have an array of size 10,000,000 and each element has 4 bytes (a 32-bit int), then that's a whopping 40 megabytes of memory. Now let's say that only half the time you need all 4 bytes, but the other half of the time you only need 2 bytes (1 short). You could use a union to get rid of those other two bytes. But it isn't worth saving those two bytes for each object in your array - it only saves 20 megs of memory at the cost of making your code much more complicated.
22/04/2022, 12:16 - Harshita jnu: This message was deleted
22/04/2022, 12:16 - Harshita jnu: Structures are better than Unions.

Structures are used to store the data in a structured manner to allow for easy access and modification of data. This is the case when we want to group related data items together and assign them a single name.

Unions are also used to store the data but the difference here is that a union can only hold a single variable at any given time. The size of a union is always equal to that of its largest member.

So, since structures can store multiple variables together and unions can hold only a single variable at any given time, it can be concluded that structures are better than unions.

25/05/2022, 20:10 - preeti jnu: *Checklist*

*1. 1+4 enrollment form ki copies (1 poora + 4 forms of only selected pages )*

*2.    2  copies of*

A. 12th marksheet
B. 12th certificate
C. 10th marksheet (certificate ho toh le aana)
D. Category proof 
E. Migration
F. Graduation degree marksheet/STATEMENT OF MARKS/ MARKS DIKHNE CHAHIYE USMEI
G. Graduation provisional certificate
I. Character certificate
J. Addhar card 
K . Any one among - Passport, Domicile or voter ID
L. Folio latest
M. Minimum 10 passport size photographs

*Important notes*

1. Jo log pehle college mei hostel the, please bring a receipt, proof, warden's statement.

2. Jo log Delhi ke hai lekin PG/flat mei the bring agreement or bijli bill anything that can prove ki you were living in rental accommodation

3. DU valo ka character certificate is in the provisional degree only.
 IT WILL WORK. NO PROBLEM

*4. Jinka gap hai, gap vala certificate is important*

*5. Agar us vakt mention Kiya tha form mei ki you are simultaneously taking a  degree then discontinue vala certificate*

6. Agar kisi ne hostel allotment ke liye NO kar diya tha but usko chahiye hostel toh don't worry, it'll work, just inform tomorrow and kal mil lena mujhse. 


*ORIGINAL DOCUMENTS REQUIRED*

1. 10 and 12 th marksheet and certificate (certificate ho toh acha hai, maang rahe hai)

2. Graduation degree/marksheet will work from internet but original provisional should be there 

3. Original migration is required, also digital will work (DU valo)

4. Orginal character certificate

5. Orginal aadhar rakh lena

*6. Orginal category proof*

28/06/2022, 12:12 - preeti jnu: Dear Students,
This is regarding the Internal Assessment of the subject Object Oriented Programming (CS-410).

There will be Two components of the Internal Assessment.

There will be a 20 marks assessment in the form of a minor test (online mode). This test will be scheduled on Last week of June 2022. You will receive the question paper through Email on the said date at 10 AM and you are supposed to submit the answer in pdf format around 12 noon same day (strict timeline) at  the email id mentioned in the question paper. The syllabus for this minor test will be from Introduction of Object Oriented Programming to Constructor Overloading.
You have to make and submit a Project in Java. This will be 20 Marks Assessment. You can make a project in the group (maximum 3 members in a group). The project is supposed to be submitted on or before August 10, 2022. There will be an online presentation for evaluation of the project where you can demonstrate the work. Originality will be an important criteria for the project.

Regards

Ratneshwer

07/10/2022, 21:12 - Aditya Mahakali: Dear Sir/Ma'am,

Greetings!

There is a great internship opportunity for final year students graduating in 2023.

Palo Alto Networks, the global leading cybersecurity company, is hiring interns through Skillenza for the roles of:

IT Software Developer Intern
Salesforce Developer Intern 
Software Engineer - Network Service - Intern
Other details:

CTC/Remuneration: 1 Lakh PM

Tenure: 6 months

Location: Remote

Palo Alto is known to be very generous with its internship remunerations. If the hired interns perform well during their internship tenure of 6 months, Palo Alto would offer them a full-time position with a significant salary jump.

Students have to register before 10th October as the tests will be conducted online on 10th October.

Open job positions:

Job Title 1: IT Software Developer Intern

CTC/Remuneration: 1 Lakh PM

Tenure: 6 months

Click here to apply here for the position



Job Title 2: Salesforce Developer Intern

CTC/Remuneration: 1 Lakh PM

Tenure: 6 months

Click here to apply here for the position



Job Title 3: Software Engineer - Network Services Intern

CTC/Remuneration: 1 Lakh PM

Tenure: 6 months

Click here to apply here for the position

More details about the requirements and Job description are available on the registration page.

What do students have to do:

Register on Skillenza before 10th October
Fill in a few more details
Take the tests on 10th October. Test duration:- Max 3 hours
Score well, and get connected with the Palo Alto team for an Interview.
Based on performance, get qualified for an internship offer
*NOTE: You have to register before 10th October as the tests will be conducted online on 10th October.

Request you to please share this opportunity with all the final year students and ask them to register.
